{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":555,"text":"In 2011, during the final six months\nof Kim Jong-Il's life,"},{"time":7029,"text":"I lived undercover in North Korea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11791,"text":"I was born and raised\nin South Korea, their enemy."},{"time":16035,"text":"I live in America, their other enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20369,"text":"Since 2002, I had visited\nNorth Korea a few times."},{"time":24942,"text":"And I had come to realize\nthat to write about it with any meaning,"},{"time":30339,"text":"or to understand the place\nbeyond the regime's propaganda,"},{"time":35411,"text":"the only option was total immersion."},{"time":42109,"text":"So I posed as a teacher and a missionary"},{"time":46360,"text":"at an all-male university in Pyongyang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54239,"text":"The Pyongyang University\nof Science and Technology"},{"time":58001,"text":"was founded by Evangelical Christians\nwho cooperate with the regime"},{"time":63958,"text":"to educate the sons\nof the North Korean elite,"},{"time":69212,"text":"without proselytizing,\nwhich is a capital crime there."},{"time":75196,"text":"The students were 270 young men,\nexpected to be the future leaders"},{"time":81921,"text":"of the most isolated and brutal\ndictatorship in existence."},{"time":88689,"text":"When I arrived, they became my students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95336,"text":"2011 was a special year,"},{"time":97642,"text":"marking the 100th anniversary of the birth\nof North Korea's original Great Leader,"},{"time":103908,"text":"Kim Il-Sung."},{"time":105869,"text":"To celebrate the occasion, the regime\nshut down all universities,"},{"time":111385,"text":"and sent students off to the fields"},{"time":114220,"text":"to build the DPRK's much-heralded ideal"},{"time":118378,"text":"as the world's most powerful\nand prosperous nation."},{"time":124958,"text":"My students were the only ones\nspared from that fate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129502,"text":"North Korea is a gulag posing as a nation."},{"time":134038,"text":"Everything there\nis about the Great Leader."},{"time":136494,"text":"Every book, every newspaper article,\nevery song, every TV program --"},{"time":141828,"text":"there is just one subject."},{"time":143970,"text":"The flowers are named after him,"},{"time":145935,"text":"the mountains are carved with his slogans."},{"time":148831,"text":"Every citizen wears the badge\nof the Great Leader at all times."},{"time":153861,"text":"Even their calendar system begins\nwith the birth of Kim Il-Sung."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159521,"text":"The school was a heavily guarded\nprison, posing as a campus."},{"time":164751,"text":"Teachers could only leave on group outings\naccompanied by an official minder."},{"time":171960,"text":"Even then, our trips were limited\nto sanctioned national monuments"},{"time":177357,"text":"celebrating the Great Leader."},{"time":180405,"text":"The students were not allowed\nto leave the campus,"},{"time":184274,"text":"or communicate with their parents."},{"time":188761,"text":"Their days were meticulously mapped out,\nand any free time they had"},{"time":192911,"text":"was devoted to honoring\ntheir Great Leader."},{"time":197421,"text":"Lesson plans had to meet the approval\nof North Korean staff,"},{"time":202452,"text":"every class was recorded and reported on,\nevery room was bugged,"},{"time":206681,"text":"and every conversation, overheard."},{"time":210743,"text":"Every blank space was covered with the \nportraits of Kim Il-Sung and Kim Jong-Il,"},{"time":216413,"text":"like everywhere else in North Korea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221092,"text":"We were never allowed\nto discuss the outside world."},{"time":223969,"text":"As students of science and technology,\nmany of them were computer majors"},{"time":229003,"text":"but they did not know\nthe existence of the Internet."},{"time":232555,"text":"They had never heard\nof Mark Zuckerberg or Steve Jobs."},{"time":237525,"text":"Facebook, Twitter -- none of those things\nwould have meant a thing."},{"time":242605,"text":"And I could not tell them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246861,"text":"I went there looking for truth."},{"time":250135,"text":"But where do you even start\nwhen an entire nation's ideology,"},{"time":253805,"text":"my students' day-to-day realities,"},{"time":255823,"text":"and even my own position\nat the universities,"},{"time":259798,"text":"were all built on lies?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265930,"text":"I started with a game."},{"time":267976,"text":"We played \"Truth and Lie.\""},{"time":270689,"text":"A volunteer would write a sentence\non the chalkboard,"},{"time":273356,"text":"and the other students had to guess"},{"time":276131,"text":"whether it was a truth or a lie."},{"time":279158,"text":"Once a student wrote, \"I visited\nChina last year on vacation,\""},{"time":283385,"text":"and everyone shouted, \"Lie!\""},{"time":287025,"text":"They all knew this wasn't possible."},{"time":289317,"text":"Virtually no North Korean is allowed\nto leave the country."},{"time":293297,"text":"Even traveling within their own country\nrequires a travel pass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300569,"text":"I had hoped that this game would reveal\nsome truth about my students,"},{"time":305870,"text":"because they lie so often and so easily,"},{"time":308957,"text":"whether about the mythical\naccomplishments of their Great Leader,"},{"time":313394,"text":"or the strange claim that they cloned\na rabbit as fifth graders."},{"time":319482,"text":"The difference between truth and lies\nseemed at times hazy to them."},{"time":324423,"text":"It took me a while to understand\nthe different types of lies;"},{"time":328538,"text":"they lie to shield their system\nfrom the world,"},{"time":331538,"text":"or they were taught lies,\nand were just regurgitating them."},{"time":335417,"text":"Or, at moments, they lied out of habit."},{"time":340314,"text":"But if all they have ever known were lies,"},{"time":344449,"text":"how could we expect them to be otherwise?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349330,"text":"Next, I tried to teach them essay writing."},{"time":352408,"text":"But that turned out to be\nnearly impossible."},{"time":355225,"text":"Essays are about coming up with\none's own thesis,"},{"time":359412,"text":"and making an evidence-based\nargument to prove it."},{"time":364044,"text":"These students, however, were\nsimply told what to think,"},{"time":367985,"text":"and they obeyed."},{"time":369800,"text":"In their world, critical thinking\nwas not allowed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374880,"text":"I also gave them the weekly assignment\nof writing a personal letter,"},{"time":379535,"text":"to anybody."},{"time":381310,"text":"It took a long time, but eventually\nsome of them began to write"},{"time":385509,"text":"to their mothers, their friends,\ntheir girlfriends."},{"time":390479,"text":"Although those were just homework,"},{"time":393496,"text":"and would never reach\ntheir intended recipients,"},{"time":397076,"text":"my students slowly began to reveal\ntheir true feelings in them."},{"time":402376,"text":"They wrote that they were fed\nup with the sameness of everything."},{"time":407435,"text":"They were worried about their future."},{"time":409787,"text":"In those letters, they rarely ever\nmentioned their Great Leader."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418806,"text":"I was spending all of my time\nwith these young men."},{"time":422558,"text":"We all ate meals together,\nplayed basketball together."},{"time":427679,"text":"I often called them gentlemen,\nwhich made them giggle."},{"time":432858,"text":"They blushed at the mention of girls."},{"time":436332,"text":"And I came to adore them."},{"time":438703,"text":"And watching them open up\neven in the tiniest of ways,"},{"time":442364,"text":"was deeply moving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445967,"text":"But something also felt wrong."},{"time":448973,"text":"During those months\nof living in their world,"},{"time":451846,"text":"I often wondered if the truth would,\nin fact, improve their lives."},{"time":459759,"text":"I wanted so much to tell them the truth,"},{"time":462874,"text":"of their country and of the outside world,"},{"time":466318,"text":"where Arab youth were turning\ntheir rotten regime inside out,"},{"time":470333,"text":"using the power of social media,"},{"time":472152,"text":"where everyone except them was\nconnected through the world wide web,"},{"time":476874,"text":"which wasn't worldwide after all."},{"time":481489,"text":"But for them, the truth was dangerous."},{"time":486955,"text":"By encouraging them to run after it,\nI was putting them at risk --"},{"time":491878,"text":"of persecution,"},{"time":494259,"text":"of heartbreak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498755,"text":"When you're not allowed to express\nanything in the open,"},{"time":501437,"text":"you become good at reading\nwhat is unspoken."},{"time":505736,"text":"In one of their personal letters to me,\na student wrote that he understood"},{"time":510784,"text":"why I always called them gentlemen."},{"time":514630,"text":"It was because I was wishing them\nto be gentle in life, he said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522767,"text":"On my last day in December of 2011,"},{"time":525568,"text":"the day Kim Jong-Il's death was announced,"},{"time":528342,"text":"their world shattered."},{"time":532798,"text":"I had to leave without a proper goodbye."},{"time":536667,"text":"But I think they knew\nhow sad I was for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540340,"text":"Once, toward the end of my stay,\na student said to me,"},{"time":544269,"text":"\"Professor, we never think of you\nas being different from us."},{"time":549767,"text":"Our circumstances are different,\nbut you're the same as us."},{"time":555898,"text":"We want you to know that we truly\nthink of you as being the same.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":565999,"text":"Today, if I could respond\nto my students with a letter of my own,"},{"time":569830,"text":"which is of course impossible,"},{"time":572330,"text":"I would tell them this:"},{"time":577876,"text":"\"My dear gentlemen,"},{"time":580550,"text":"It's been a bit over three years\nsince I last saw you."},{"time":583549,"text":"And now, you must be 22 --\nmaybe even as old as 23."},{"time":588565,"text":"At our final class, I asked you\nif there was anything you wanted."},{"time":593822,"text":"The only wish you expressed,\nthe only thing you ever asked of me"},{"time":597265,"text":"in all those months we spent together,"},{"time":600707,"text":"was for me to speak to you in Korean."},{"time":603160,"text":"Just once."},{"time":605084,"text":"I was there to teach you English;"},{"time":607584,"text":"you knew it wasn't allowed."},{"time":610144,"text":"But I understood then, you wanted\nto share that bond of our mother tongue."},{"time":618052,"text":"I called you my gentlemen,"},{"time":621306,"text":"but I don't know if being gentle\nin Kim Jong-Un's merciless North Korea"},{"time":625751,"text":"is a good thing."},{"time":627717,"text":"I don't want you to lead a revolution --"},{"time":630068,"text":"let some other young person do it."},{"time":633035,"text":"The rest of the world might casually\nencourage or even expect"},{"time":636605,"text":"some sort of North Korean Spring,"},{"time":638979,"text":"but I don't want you to do anything risky,"},{"time":641525,"text":"because I know in your world,\nsomeone is always watching."},{"time":647027,"text":"I don't want to imagine\nwhat might happen to you."},{"time":650225,"text":"If my attempts to reach you have\ninspired something new in you,"},{"time":655191,"text":"I would rather you forget me."},{"time":657646,"text":"Become soldiers of your Great Leader,\nand live long, safe lives."},{"time":664361,"text":"You once asked me if I thought\nyour city of Pyongyang was beautiful,"},{"time":669084,"text":"and I could not answer truthfully then."},{"time":673609,"text":"But I know why you asked."},{"time":675493,"text":"I know that it was important for you\nto hear that I, your teacher,"},{"time":680048,"text":"the one who has seen the world\nthat you are forbidden from,"},{"time":683933,"text":"declare your city as the most beautiful."},{"time":689793,"text":"I know hearing that would make\nyour lives there a bit more bearable,"},{"time":694972,"text":"but no, I don't find\nyour capital beautiful."},{"time":698900,"text":"Not because it's monotone and concrete,"},{"time":701553,"text":"but because of what it symbolizes:"},{"time":703440,"text":"a monster that feeds off\nthe rest of the country,"},{"time":708297,"text":"where citizens are soldiers and slaves."},{"time":713734,"text":"All I see there is darkness."},{"time":717932,"text":"But it's your home, so I cannot hate it."},{"time":721623,"text":"And I hope instead that you,\nmy lovely young gentlemen,"},{"time":726684,"text":"will one day help make it beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730970,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732183,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}